CONDITIONS OF TRAVEL
BAGGAGE-Per passenger, two pieces of checked
baggage, total length, width, and height of each not to
exceed 62 inches (157cm), total length, width, and
height of both combined not to exceed 107 inches
(272cm). No piece may weigh over 50 pounds. First
piece guaranteed space on the scheduled flight; second
Diece on a space available basis.
EXCESS BAGGAGE CHARGES- In excess of
baggage allowance or oversized baggage, $10.00 per
piece, on a space available basis.
BAGGAGE LIABILITY-$500.00 per passenger; all
baggage claims must be submitted immediately.
RESTRICTED ARTICLES -Corrosive liquids,
flammable substances, such as matches and lighter
fluid, compressed gas or any hazardous material may
not be carried in baggage.
CHECK IN TIME -Passengers must be checked in
at least ten minutes prior to the scheduled departure
of the flight, or the reservation may be cancelled.
RESPONSIBILITIES FOR DEPARTURES,
ARRIVAL, CONNECTIONS AND CANCEL.
LATIONS-SFO Helicopter Airlines will not be
responsible for damages resulting from failure to depart
or arrive at times stated in the timetable, nor for errors
herein, nor for failure to make connections with planes
of other airlines or of this company, nor for cancellations
CREDIT CARDS.
- SFO Helicopter Airlines accepts
American Express, Diners Club, Carte Blanche,
Master Card, VISA and UATP.
TICKETING-Tickets may be purchased from your
travel agent, corporate traffic manager, any scheduled
airlines, or any SFO HELICOPTER AIRLINES ticket
CONNECTION TIME- Please allow a minimum
of 30 minutes to connect with a United flight; 45
minutes for all other airlines
